0px;"><font style="font-size: 15px;">Receive Synchronization from a Listener Perspective</font></h1><div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;">SonoBusMendeni supports receive synchronization to improve the listening experience. When the Sync Receive button is pushed&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; , all streams from remote players are synchronized to the listener. By measuring receive latency from each player and noting the largest value, the receive jitter buffer can be padded to compensate. The calculation is:</font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><br></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;">deltaMs = maxrecvMs - currentRecvMs</font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;">newJitterBuffer = currentJitterBuffer + deltaMs</font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><br></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;">Where maxrecvMs is the largest receive latency in the set of remote peers. An extra 2ms of padding is also added to improve overall listening experience by preventing drops that might be on the ragged edge.</font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><br></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;">In our example session, 55ms is the largest receive latency (Pink player) from the three Remote Musicians. Adding 2ms for extra padding, maxrecvMs is 57.</font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><br></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;">Let's say the Orange player has currentJitterBuffer value of 8ms:</font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><br></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;">45 = 57 - 12</font></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">53 =&nbsp; 8 + 45</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">The new jitter buffer value is set to 53ms. This is all done on the listener side - players are unaware as nothing changes from their perspective. Latency between session players is unchanged.</span></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><br></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;">The result is a close to perfect listening experience regardless of where the audience is located. Successful synchronization is highly dependent on stable connections for all players and the listener.</font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><br></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;">The receive sync button can be pushed to force a recalibration of maxrecvMs when new players arrive/leave or network conditions change. Resetting in the middle of a song is not recommended as recalibration can be audible.</font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><br></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;">Local Musicians can also participate by using headphones for a traditional SonoBus session experience (shown) or play along to the synchronized House PA (not show). Playing with the PA will increase overall latency to the other remote players, but they can turn down the venue musician(s) to reduce distraction.</font></div></div>" vertex="1"> <mxGeometry height="828" width="400" x="434" y="27" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="MMU7wC4jm6lLepNU2r36-31" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="SonoBus "Player"" vertex="1"> <mxGeometry height="57" width="129" x="263" y="425" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="MMU7wC4jm6lLepNU2r36-32" edge="1" parent="1" source="MMU7wC4jm6lLepNU2r36-31" style="endArrow=classic;startArrow=none;html=1;rounded=0;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;strokeColor=light-dark(#000000,#3399FF);strokeWidth=2;entryX=0.682;entryY=-0.1;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;entryPerimeter=0;startFill=0;" target="MMU7wC4jm6lLepNU2r36-29" value=""> <mxGeometry height="50" relative="1" width="50" as="geometry"> <Array as="points" /> <mxPoint x="330" y="360" as="sourcePoint" /> <mxPoint x="378" y="549" as="targetPoint" /> </mxGeometry> </mxCell> <mxCell id="MMU7wC4jm6lLepNU2r36-33" parent="1" style="shape=image;verticalLabelPosition=bottom;labelBackgroundColor=default;verticalAlign=top;aspect=fixed;imageAspect=0;editableCssRules=.*;image=data:image/svg+xml,;" value="" vertex="1"> <mxGeometry height="18.45" width="17" x="485" y="112.55000000000001" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="wqusKDDBDGM86phBFI-r-1" parent="1" style="shape=image;verticalLabelPosition=bottom;labelBackgroundColor=default;verticalAlign=top;aspect=fixed;imageAspect=0;editableCssRules=.*;image=data:image/svg+xml,;" value="" vertex="1"> <mxGeometry height="47.8" width="44.03" x="120" y="299.2" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> </root> </mxGraphModel> </diagram> </mxfile>

h1.font: Receive Synchronization from a Listener Perspective

div.font: SonoBusMendeni supports receive synchronization to improve the listening experience. When the Sync Receive button is pushed , all streams from remote players are synchronized to the listener. By measuring receive latency from each player and noting the largest value, the receive jitter buffer can be padded to compensate. The calculation is:

Where maxrecvMs is the largest receive latency in the set of remote peers. An extra 2ms of padding is also added to improve overall listening experience by preventing drops that might be on the ragged edge.
In our example session, 55ms is the largest receive latency (Pink player) from the three Remote Musicians. Adding 2ms for extra padding, maxrecvMs is 57.
Let's say the Orange player has currentJitterBuffer value of 8ms:

div.span: The new jitter buffer value is set to 53ms. This is all done on the listener side - players are unaware as nothing changes from their perspective. Latency between session players is unchanged.

div.font: The result is a close to perfect listening experience regardless of where the audience is located. Successful synchronization is highly dependent on stable connections for all players and the listener.

The receive sync button can be pushed to force a recalibration of maxrecvMs when new players arrive/leave or network conditions change. Resetting in the middle of a song is not recommended as recalibration can be audible.

Local Musicians can also participate by using headphones for a traditional SonoBus session experience (shown) or play along to the synchronized House PA (not show). Playing with the PA will increase overall latency to the other remote players, but they can turn down the venue musician(s) to reduce distraction.
